The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as feature detection and matching, which are typically associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a pre-trained CNN, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The method proposed in the paper involves computing the gradient of the feature map, which is a common technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on image datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
